# Apartment ERP — Environment Variables

**Copy to `.env` and fill in required values:**
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

---

## REQUIRED — fill in before running

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:5432/test
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=run: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3001
APP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001
```

---

## APPLICATION

```env
NODE_ENV=development               # development | production
COOKIE_SECURE=false             # true in production (HTTPS only)
CRON_ENABLED=true
OUTBOX_ENABLED=true
CRON_SECRET=your-cron-secret
PORT=3001
```

---

## SECRETS

```env
AUTH_SECRET=minimum-32-chars-secret
INVOICE_ACCESS_SECRET=...
FILE_ACCESS_SECRET=...
```

---

## REDIS [OPTIONAL]

Redis is optional. Without it the app uses an in-memory rate limiter.
```env
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379    # or redis://redis:6379/1 in Docker
```

---

## LINE MESSAGING [OPTIONAL]

Get credentials from https://developers.line.biz/

```env
LINE_CHANNEL_ID=
LINE_CHANNEL_SECRET=
LINE_ACCESS_TOKEN=           # long-lived token
LINE_USER_ID=                # your LINE user ID for testing
```

---

## SENTRY [OPTIONAL]

```env
SENTRY_DSN=
```

---

## BACKUP [OPTIONAL]

```env
BACKUP_CRON=0 3 * * *
BACKUP_RETENTION_DAYS=7
BACKUP_S3_BUCKET=
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=
```

---

## MONITORING

```env
METRICS_TOKEN=               # Bearer token for /api/metrics (optional)
GRAFANA_ADMIN_USER=admin
GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123
```
